@node INTRO "Introduction"

 1 - Introduction
 ================

 BeatIt is a netbeat clock for AmigaOS. It displays
 the so called "beat" in a small window on the desktop.

 One day consists of 1000 beats.

 The beat was invented by Swatchģ, a watchmaker located
 in switzerland.

@endnode


@node USAGE "Usage"

 2 - Usage
 =========

 First make sure that you have the times.font installed in
 your FONTS: directory.

 Simply start BeatIt from Workbench. You can also start it
 from CLI or WBStartup...

 Please take a look on the timezone-settings in the
 preferences.

 To quit BeatIt klick the top-left of the window.

@endnode


@node PREFS "Preferences"

 3 - Preferences
 ===============

 Since version 2 of BeatIt there is the BeatIt-Preferences
 tool BeatItPrefs.

 With it you can simply modify the following things:

 GUI - Changes the look of BeatIt.

   You can choose between original-, workbench and
   digital-mode.


 X/Y position - changes the window position

   Enter the correct values for X- and Y-Coordinates


 Timezone - enter correct timezone

     If you are not living in a country where GMT is valid,
     you have to set the timezone you are living in. This is
     the offset from GMT in the Īhhmm format.

     A correct value for e.g. Germany is +0100

     Important! There is no summer-/wintertime in beats! So
                make sure you added one hour if you are
                living in a zone where summertime is ACTUALLY
                valid (in this case +0200).

 Important! Version 2 of BeatIt doesn't need the environment-
            variable "TZ" which can be deleted.

@endnode


@node CONV "BeatItConv"

 4 - BeatItConv
 ==============

 BeatItConv is a tool to calculate normal time into beats
 and the other way around.

 To start BeatItConv doubleclick its icon.

 To calculate time into beats, simply enter the minutes
 and seconds in the correct gadgets and start calculting
 with "ConvTime"

 To calculate beats to time enter the number of beats in
 the beat-gadget and start calculating with "ConvBeat"

 To quit BeatItConv close its window.

@endnode


@node BUGS "Bugs"

 5 - Bugs
 ========

 Yes, of course :-)

 - There will be two Enforcer-hits when starting BeatIt.
   This is a bug in ACE when opening a font :-(

 - If x/y values are too high BeatIt crashes.

@endnode


